Downloading the kernel from Kernel.org or by using the below command!

wget https://git.kernel.org/torvalds/t/linux-xxxxxxxx.tar.gz (Choose the latest/stable tar file)

Extracting the source:

tar xvzf linux-xxxxxxx.tar.gz (replace xxxxxx ---> version number)



Configuring the kernel:

cp /boot/config-$(uname -r) .config

run make command

Compiling and installing: 

make modules_install

sudo make install


Enable the kernel for boot:

sudo update-initramfs -c -k xxxxxxx (Replace xxxxx ----> version numbr)

sudo update-grub


CONGRADUALTIONS!!!!!!!!!!! 

You've Complied the Kernel! :) 
